<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1517,2084]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,483,1517,1543]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Cultural characteristics:</emphasis>
Colonies on OA transparent, white, reaching 
<quantity box="[1000,1080,1517,1544]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="39.0">39 mm</quantity>
diam after 1 wk at 23–25 °C, on PDA with a white surface and pale brown reverse, reaching 
<quantity box="[799,877,1553,1580]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
diam after 1 wk at 23–25 °C, on SNA white surface and white reverse, reaching 
<quantity box="[457,537,1589,1616]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 mm</quantity>
diam after 1 wk at 23–25 °C. On SNA- barley seed, and WA- 
<taxonomicName box="[1256,1349,1589,1615]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Cyperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Cyperus</taxonomicName>
leaf was consisting of smooth, hyaline, branched, septate hyphae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
