<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1517,2084]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,253,1733,1760]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,243,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Note</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
The morphology and molecular methodologies were proved the two isolates obtained from sedge plants are relatedness to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klaubauf, Lebrun &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2014" box="[298,506,1769,1795]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,506,1769,1795]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Pseudopyricularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus and confirmed as new species. BLASTn search with the generated sequence of the ex‒ 
<typeStatus box="[248,296,1806,1832]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
strain (
<collectingCountry box="[380,450,1805,1831]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">IRAN</collectingCountry>
3988 
<collectionCode box="[516,534,1805,1831]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
) showed high similarities to 
<taxonomicName box="[859,1058,1805,1831]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bothriochloae">
<emphasis box="[859,1058,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. bothriochloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strain 
<accessionNumber box="[1134,1265,1805,1832]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/CPC21650" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<collectionCode box="[1134,1187,1805,1831]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3snx-0r7t" name="Culture collection of Pedro Crous" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">CPC</collectionCode>
21650
</accessionNumber>
[(
<collectionCode box="[1288,1336,1805,1831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">ITS</collectionCode>
: Identities = 503/520 (97%), gaps= 4/520(0%)), (28 
<collectionCode box="[606,622,1841,1867]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
: Identities = 803/8 06(99%), gaps = 1/806(0%)), and (
<emphasis box="[1242,1307,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<collectionCode box="[1242,1296,1841,1867]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">RPB</collectionCode>
1
</emphasis>
: Identities = 671/672(99%), gaps = 0/672(0%))] and to 
<taxonomicName box="[610,778,1877,1903]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyrcaniana">
<emphasis box="[610,778,1877,1903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hyrcaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strain 
<collectingCountry box="[853,921,1878,1904]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">IRAN</collectingCountry>
2760 
<collectionCode box="[984,1002,1877,1903]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
[(
<emphasis box="[1027,1078,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<collectionCode box="[1027,1078,1878,1904]" country="India" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12692" name="Botanical Survey of India" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">CAL</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
: Identities = 366/414(88%), gaps = 17/414(4%))]. The new species can easily be distinguished from other species in the genus, in terms of different size and shape of conidia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Javan-Nikkhah, A. Pordel &amp; G. Ghorbani" authorityYear="2021" box="[435,608,1949,1975]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hedjaroudii">
<emphasis box="[435,608,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hedjaroudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[772,940,1949,1975]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyrcaniana">
<emphasis box="[772,940,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hyrcaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1155,1949,1975]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bothriochloae">
<emphasis box="[956,1155,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. bothriochloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1422,1949,1975]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caffra">
<emphasis box="[1218,1422,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Pyricularia caffra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1-septate conidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Pordel, A. &amp; Khodaparast, S. A. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Javan-Nikkhah, M." box="[344,555,1985,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" pagination="729 - 736" refId="ref6347" refString="Pordel, A., Khodaparast, S. A., McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Javan-Nikkhah, M. (2017) Two new species of Pseudopyricularia from Iran. Mycological Progress 16: 729 - 736. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 017 - 1307 - z" type="journal article" year="2017">
Pordel 
<emphasis box="[428,486,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). However, the conidia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Javan-Nikkhah, A. Pordel &amp; G. Ghorbani" authorityYear="2021" box="[857,1031,1985,2011]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hedjaroudii">
<emphasis box="[857,1031,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hedjaroudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in length from 
<taxonomicName box="[1281,1452,1985,2011]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyrcaniana">
<emphasis box="[1281,1452,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hyrcaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
((17–)20–29(−31) µm), 
<taxonomicName box="[408,607,2021,2047]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bothriochloae">
<emphasis box="[408,607,2021,2047]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. bothriochloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
((18–)19–22(–23) µm) and 
<taxonomicName box="[926,1036,2021,2047]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caffra">
<emphasis box="[926,1036,2021,2047]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Py. caffra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(20–31.5 µm). Conidiophores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Javan-Nikkhah, A. Pordel &amp; G. Ghorbani" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hedjaroudii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hedjaroudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more prolonged than of the 
<taxonomicName box="[628,797,2057,2083]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyrcaniana">
<emphasis box="[628,797,2057,2083]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. hyrcaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(65–125(−140) µm), 
<taxonomicName box="[1042,1241,2057,2083]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bothriochloae">
<emphasis box="[1042,1241,2057,2083]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ps. bothriochloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(90–180 µm), and 
<taxonomicName box="[136,246,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caffra">
<emphasis box="[136,246,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Py. caffra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(45–100(–175) µm). Besides, conidia shape of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Javan-Nikkhah, A. Pordel &amp; G. Ghorbani" authorityYear="2021" box="[790,963,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hedjaroudii">
<emphasis box="[790,963,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Ps. hedjaroudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1115,1225,158,184]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caffra">
<emphasis box="[1115,1225,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Py. caffra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Matsushima, T." box="[1240,1447,158,184]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" refId="ref5921" refString="Matsushima, T. (1993) Matsushima mycological memoirs. 7. Matsushima, Kobe, Japan, 75 pp." type="book" year="1993">Matsushima 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa, F. R. &amp; Gusmao, L. F. P. &amp; Barbosa, E. F. F." box="[136,359,194,220]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" pagination="29 - 36" refId="ref4043" refString="Barbosa, F. R., Gusmao, L. F. P. &amp; Barbosa, E. F. F. (2008) Fungos anamorficos (Hyphomycetes) no Semi-arido do Estado da Bahia, Brasil. Acta Botanica Brasilia 22: 29 - 36." type="journal article" year="2008">
Barbosa 
<emphasis box="[235,291,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">
Phylogenetic analyses revealed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klaubauf, Lebrun &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2014" box="[545,753,230,256]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[545,753,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Pseudopyricularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus is the sister group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klaubauf, M.-H.Lebrun &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2014" box="[1065,1269,231,256]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Macgarvieomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1269,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Macgarvieomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klaubauf, S. &amp; Tharreau, D. &amp; Fournier, E. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; de Vries, R. P. &amp; Lebrun, M. H." pageId="8" pageNumber="103" pagination="85 - 120" refId="ref5842" refString="Klaubauf, S., Tharreau, D., Fournier, E., Groenewald, J. Z., Crous, P. W., de Vries, R. P. &amp; Lebrun, M. H. (2014) Resolving the polyphyletic nature of Pyricularia (Pyriculariaceae). Studies in Mycology 79: 85 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. simyco. 2014.09.004" type="journal article" year="2014">
Klaubauf 
<emphasis box="[1396,1452,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pordel, A. &amp; Khodaparast, S. A. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Javan-Nikkhah, M." box="[208,419,266,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" pagination="729 - 736" refId="ref6347" refString="Pordel, A., Khodaparast, S. A., McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Javan-Nikkhah, M. (2017) Two new species of Pseudopyricularia from Iran. Mycological Progress 16: 729 - 736. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 017 - 1307 - z" type="journal article" year="2017">
Pordel 
<emphasis box="[291,349,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klaubauf, M.-H.Lebrun &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2014" box="[440,644,267,292]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Macgarvieomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[440,644,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Macgarvieomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klaubauf, Lebrun &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2014" box="[903,1111,266,292]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,1111,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Pseudopyricularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1170,1452,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1299,266,292]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Pyricularia</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1452,267,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
based on the morphology and phylogeny criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="Klaubauf, S. &amp; Tharreau, D. &amp; Fournier, E. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; de Vries, R. P. &amp; Lebrun, M. H." box="[698,935,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" pagination="85 - 120" refId="ref5842" refString="Klaubauf, S., Tharreau, D., Fournier, E., Groenewald, J. Z., Crous, P. W., de Vries, R. P. &amp; Lebrun, M. H. (2014) Resolving the polyphyletic nature of Pyricularia (Pyriculariaceae). Studies in Mycology 79: 85 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. simyco. 2014.09.004" type="journal article" year="2014">
Klaubauf 
<emphasis box="[812,869,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pordel, A. &amp; Khodaparast, S. A. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Javan-Nikkhah, M." box="[947,1153,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" pagination="729 - 736" refId="ref6347" refString="Pordel, A., Khodaparast, S. A., McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Javan-Nikkhah, M. (2017) Two new species of Pseudopyricularia from Iran. Mycological Progress 16: 729 - 736. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 017 - 1307 - z" type="journal article" year="2017">
Pordel 
<emphasis box="[1028,1085,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). In phylogenetic trees 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Javan-Nikkhah, A. Pordel &amp; G. Ghorbani" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hedjaroudii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Ps. hedjaroudii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well-separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[530,729,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bothriochloae">
<emphasis box="[530,729,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Ps. bothriochloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[743,911,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyrcaniana">
<emphasis box="[743,911,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">Ps. hyrcaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis box="[973,1147,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName box="[973,1143,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pyriculariaceae" genus="Pseudopyricularia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Magnaporthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hagahagae">Ps. hagahagae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
